Class TilePart.Construct

    public static class TilePart.Construct
extends SourceData
implements TilePart
    Any part of a tile declaration (that is not a reference to another tile). Obviously this should be referencing a Table.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Construct

        public Construct(Source source)
          throws LevelLuaException.Runtime
        Construct a miscellaneous tile part from a Source object. On construction the given source is checked, if it really references a table. Then Constants.checkTable is applied to the table, to convert any integers, that can be represented by constants.
        Parameters:
        source - source to be referenced by a tile declaration via this object.
        Throws:
        LevelLuaException.Runtime - indicates, that the given source is not a Table.
